Feel-good film where a poor and pregnant Ricky Lake survives a train crash and wakes up with a filthy rich Shirley MacLaine as her mother-in-law, and Brendan Fraser's twin as her husband.
Some of the comment writers on imdb are disappointed with Ricky Lake's performance as an actor, but Shirley has a field day, and Brendan Fraser is never dull.

I don't understand why there is no torrent for this movie, and apologize on behalf of the American DVD producers with the irritating habit of cutting the widescreen. (Called 'Re-formatted to fit your TV' - most TVs now are WIDESCREEN!!!)

DVDrip, 2-pass XviD fullscreen 624x464, great stereo AC3
Burn tested, runs well in both my standalone DivX players.
